Colombia Workers Rescued After Coal Mine Collapse, Tiempo Says

-- B y   H e a t h e r   W a l s h
-- 
2011-05-17T21:18:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/colombia-workers-rescued-after-coal-mine-collapse-tiempo-says.html
Colombian rescuers freed eight
workers who were trapped for seven hours in a coal mine,  El
Tiempo  newspaper reported on its website, citing firefighter
Alveiro Gutierrez, who led the rescue.  The men appear to be in good health following a cave-in
this morning at the Lomagorda mine in western  Colombia  near the
city of Cali, the Bogota-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Heather Walsh at 
 hlwalsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net  